cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes user conversations in on-line social media and their evolution over time. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a dynamic model to predict the growth dynamics and structural properties of conversation threads. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the underlying rules for on-line conversations in different social media websites. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques to analyze user comments and conversations. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is also possible as the paper deals with social media and user interactions.
